                                                                                                                       7                                        Bhutia to return
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT              Bhaichung Bhutia                      
	New Delhi: India captain Bhaichung Bhutia, will be heading back home from national teams training camp, in Portugal, on Friday.         
	It has been learnt that Indian captain, who missed training for the past couple of days due to fever, is suffering from thyroid problems. According to reliable sources, the national team will miss Bhaichungs services during the international friendlies, scheduled in September.         
	The team, coached by Bob Houghton, is currently in Viera for a month-long training camp as a part of their preparations for the Asian Cup final round in Doha next year.         
	The captain was doing well initially, but has suddenly developed fever, said a source. There has also been a recurrence of thyroid problems due to which he has lost five kilos. He is very weak and has been advised rest. He will only join the national team during the next camp in November, the source added.         
	Some of the other senior players are also suffering from injuries. Senior midfielder Climax Lawrence is yet to recover from an ankle injury while defender Samir Naik, too, has missed training because of a calf muscle problem.                                                                                                                     
